**Intro** — rephrased to cover all three modes (disagreement, temperament,
  scope), not just disagreement.

**§2** — combined demographic flip + death spiral into a single bullet (the
  demographic flip *arms* the spiral). Loss-of-price-discovery rephrased to
  "price-insensitive flow dominates the *marginal* trade," with a footnote
  citing Mike Green / Vincent Deluard.

**§3** — cut the "what is interest?" digression, ended on the
  consensus-mortality line.

**§5** — rewrote the front-running bullet as the contrarian trade (buy what
  passive has *abandoned* — Uranium, Energy, deleted index names, ESG-dumped
  sectors). Updated the section header to match.

**§6** — full rewrite around "option tail wags the equity dog." Removed the
  "half" framing, removed "smart money," reframed as classical TA developed
  for a pre-options market. IV is now described as more informative than the
  price delta itself.

**§7** — passive flow now "*one* mechanical driver" alongside cheap-capital
  era and deteriorating quality mix. Added the pump-and-dump / insider
  trading / poor 10-year survival texture, framed as unsuitable for
  long-term investing.

**§8** — left as-is per your "keep vague" reply.

**§12** — kept "(attributed)" on the Keynes quote. Changed "traders" →
  "investors."

**§13** — relabeled as "front ratio call spread." Made explicit that
  unbounded upside risk is the *feature* (it's intentionally a short
  position with extra price + time room for error). Added the
  high-IV-and-high-price prerequisite, and the explanation of why put-side
  structures don't work at that point (puts re-priced too rich on the same
  vol expansion).

**§14** — added the "this is advanced, SPY is the entry-level default"
  bridge, requiring regime conviction first. Added explicit defence of the
  deep-ITM LEAP framing: 3x delta on 1/3 of capital, max loss is the
  premium, freed-up 2/3 sits in actual cash.

**§15** — added the bridge sentence "rotate the exposure, not the tax lot"
  tying back to §5. Wash-sale bullet rewritten as "substantially similar but
  not substantially identical" — small option friction or skew/gap risk
  introduced deliberately, with explicit US-tax disclaimer and "get a tax
  professional to bless the structure."

**§16** — CN/HK uninvestability doubled down: explicit categorical rule
  about communist government and private ownership, framed as holding until
  the political system itself changes (not a quarterly contrarian call).
  Taiwan softened to "TSMC plus the semi supply chain (MediaTek, Hon Hai,
  ASE)." Conclusion bullet sharpened: the point is **US-listed companies**
  (best-in-class businesses), not "the US market" as an index abstraction.

**§17** — renamed "Dragon-inspired shape." Foregrounded that it's modified
  from Cole, the take from Cole is the broader asset-class palette +
  vol-as-asset-class, the modification is regime-weighted allocations rather
  than static all-weather. Fixed the "small *short* tail-hedge" wording.

**Closing** — restructured around vision / strategy / tactics with the
  military framing. Vision = SOUL.md (regime/conviction layer above
  strategy). Strategy = macro positioning. Tactics = security selection (CFA
  bottom-up) + execution (your toolkit). Made explicit that CFA covers
  security-selection well, strategy poorly, vision/execution almost not at
  all — which is exactly the gap the course fills.

